==English==
===Noun===
'''hardware''' (''uncountable'')

# [[Metal]] implements.
# [[Firearm]].
# Electronic equipment.
# The part of a computer that is fixed and cannot be altered without replacement or physical modification; motherboard, expansion cards, etc.  Compare [[software]].

#* '''1955''': In electronic digital computers, telephone switching systems, [etc] .... It is not always easy to determine the factorization which is the simplest from the point of view of "'''hardware'''." &mdash; ''Some Mathematical Aspects of Switching'', Franz Hohn, in The American Mathematical Monthly, vol. 62, no. 2 (Feb. 1955), pp 75-90.

